1.notes: -5% from top set to final backoff @7.

Be wary of the suggested loads day 1 if we have never adjusted the 1RM for this exercise. It will grab the 1RM from your comp bench and likely overprescribe. If you know your 1RM for incline, set it. If not, just go by RPE and then set it afterwards using the E1RM button.

Rest = RPE-5. For each set, you'll keep the same weight, but adjust your rest period accordingly. If the set is RPE6, then you have 1 minute. If it's 7, then you have 3 minutes. Expect RPE to climb throughout the sets.
If you don't have cables, you can use DB's here, or even bands if you can set them up to give enough resistance.

2.notes: Myo-reps: x15@9->x4@10, 1 Activation. Choose a weight that will give you parameter 1 (x15@9). Perform x15@9, then take 5-6 breath rest. Keep the same weight and do x4. Repeat 5-6 breath rest and x4 set until x4 is @10 RPE. That's 1 activation.
If you don't have a back extension, light Jefferson curls with either a barbell or DB's will work here.

12 min core circuit. Just adding 1 minute from last block! Open ended sets/reps. Choose 2-4 core exercises you like, and circuit through them for 11 min. Take short breaks and rests as necessary throughout, no need to absolutely blow yourself up cardio-wise. Some of my faves are: planks, deadbugs, and side bends.

If you don't have DB's you can use a barbell, just ensure you're treating this as a lighter, more movement/pump focused slot.
